      {
        "id": 4046362,
        "name": "\u0104\u0146\u0257\u0157\u0119\u0175 \u0136\u013c\u03cb\u01e5",
        "username": "Andrew_K",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/andrew_k/{size}/279879_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-04-05T01:33:06.122Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Surprised not to see a single thread here about this unicorn. It\u2019s basically private label DRC Monty as Sarl gets a demi-muid in lieu of payment on a villa rental agreement and bottles and sells some of it. Since it doesn\u2019t say DRC it\u2019s 1/10th of the price.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=4612799&amp;iNote=10407173\"><b>2013 Garaudet Pere &amp; Fils Montrachet</b></a> - France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Montrachet Grand Cru (4/4/2023)<br>\nPnP. Lovely round nose with a precise palate, surprisingly nice acid and a wonderful dry extract on the long finish. Continues to develop over time to reveal pineapple and tropical fruit on the nose. This is drinking beautifully now and transcends the soft vintage with an abundance of acid backbone. WOTN for everyone. <b>(95 points)</b>\n</li>\n</ul>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 6,
        "updated_at": "2023-04-05T01:33:48.601Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
